cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.PE

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper analyzes the performance of a wireless sensor in terms of information transmission and energy harvesting rate, which falls under the scope of information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper considers a stochastic geometry network and analyzes the performance of a wireless sensor in such a network, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper analyzes the performance of a battery-free wireless sensor powered by ambient RF energy harvesting, which falls under the scope of systems and control. 
4. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems): The paper considers the distribution of ambient RF sources as a Ginibre alpha-determinantal point process, which falls under the scope of multiagent systems. 
5. cs.PE (Performance): The paper aims to analyze the performance of a battery-free wireless sensor powered by ambient RF energy harvesting, which falls under the scope of performance evaluation.
